{
    "id": "491",
    "title": "PERC Rule for Pulmonary Embolism",
    "desc": "The PERC Rule for Pulmonary Embolism Rules out PE if no criteria are present and pre-test probability is ≤15%.",
    "data": {
        "orgreference": [
            {
                "href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15304025",
                "text": "Kline JA, et al. Clinical criteria to prevent unnecessary diagnostic testing in emergency department patients with suspected pulmonary embolism. J Thromb Haemost 2004; 2: 1247–55."
            }
        ],
        "other_refer": [],
        "evidence": "<p>If any of the following is/are present, PE cannot be ruled out:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Age &ge;50.</li>\n<li>HR &ge;100.</li>\n<li>O₂ sat on room air&nbsp;&lt;95%.</li>\n<li>Unilateral leg swelling.</li>\n<li>Hemoptysis.</li>\n<li>Recent trauma or surgery.</li>\n<li>Prior PE or DVT.</li>\n<li>Hormone use (oral contraceptives, hormone replacement or estrogenic hormones use in males or female patients).</li>\n</ul>",
        "facts": "<p>If any criteria are positive, the PERC rule is not satisfied and cannot be used to rule out PE in this patient.</p>",
        "estimation": [],
        "primary_complains": [
            "Chest Pain",
            "Cough",
            "Shortness of Breath"
        ],
        "disease_treated": [
            "Deep Venous Thrombosis",
            "Pulmonary Embolism"
        ],
        "logic": "var calc_output=[]; \n\nvar calc_msg=''; \nvar mini_msg=''; \nvar yesno=''; \nvar output_score=(parseInt(age)+parseInt(hr)+parseInt(o2)+parseInt(dvt_pe_history)+parseInt(trauma)+parseInt(hemoptysis)+parseInt(estrogen)+parseInt(leg_swelling)); \nif (output_score == 0) { \n    yesno = 'Yes'; \n    calc_msg = 'No need for further workup, as <2% chance of PE.<br/><br/>If no criteria are positive and clinician\\u2019s pre-test probability is <15%, PERC Rule criteria are satisfied.'; \n    mini_msg='PE can be ruled out.'; \n} else { \n    yesno = 'No'; \n    calc_msg = 'If any criteria are positive, the PERC rule cannot be used to rule out PE in this patient.'; \n    mini_msg='PE cannot be ruled out.'; \n} \n\ncalc_output.push({\n    name:'mini',\n    value:yesno,\n    value_text:' ',\n    message:mini_msg\n}); \ncalc_output.push({\n    name:'347_PERC Rule_result',\n    value:output_score,\n    value_text:'criteria',\n    message:calc_msg\n});",
